[{"id":"VR598636","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<p class=\"lead_in\"><span class=\"mandatory_credit_line\"></span>The images show two views of the Vietnam Veterans Memorial, Washington, D.C., U.S., designed by Maya Lin in 1982 <span class=\"time_abbreviation\">C.E.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Describe <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">at least one</span> visual characteristic of the Vietnam Memorial.</p>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Describe the specific physical placement of the Vietnam Memorial.</p>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Using <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">two</span> examples of visual and/or contextual evidence, explain how Maya Linâ€™s design of the memorial relates to her ideas about the effect of the Vietnam War on the American people.</p>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Using specific contextual evidence, explain how the memorial was controversial at the time it was created.</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR598636_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<p class=\"lead_in\"><span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold text_decoration:underline\">Question<strong> </strong></span><strong><span class=\"compose_parent_reference scope:tcs:numberItems\"></span> refers to the following two images.</strong></p>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a photograph of the Vietnam Veterans Memorial in Washington, D.C. The photograph shows people in the distance standing on the path leading from the National Mall to the memorial.\" height=\"268\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR598636.g10.png\" width=\"400\" /><span class=\"mandatory_credit_line\">Getty Images</span></div>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\">&nbsp;</div>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a photograph of a section of the Vietnam Veterans Memorial in Washington, D.C. The photograph shows a group of visitors standing next to the wall of the memorial. The visitors appear to be pointing and reading the list of names written on the memorial. The visitors and the surrounding environment are reflected in the memorial wall. The Washington Monument is shown in the background.\" height=\"268\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR598636.g12.png\" width=\"400\" /><span class=\"mandatory_credit_line\">Ian Dagnall / Alamy Stock Photo</span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">&nbsp;</p>\n"}]}]